The Sun, Moon, Night, Day, Dawn and Evening were also Gods and Goddesses
sent by Arámfè, who is often spoken of as God. But a higher and very
distant Being is mentioned by some of the Priests.

Oíbo means White Man.

Okpéllè is a charm used in the divination of Ífa.

The final N is as in bon, and French pronunciation is nearly correct in
all the above names.

